metadata.title: Panic! At The Disco: Don't Threaten Me With A Good Time
metadata.creator: Fueled by Ramen

tracks.text: Text, Panic! at the Disco presents, Don't Threaten Me With a Good Time. Starring Brendon Urie.
We look down at our hands, holding makeup. In the mirror, we see ourselves, a thin brunette woman in our 20's wearing a low cut, short dress.
We open an app with a map on our phone.
In late afternoon, we get into a black car.
At a club, people dance.
We sit at a bar, and hold up one finger to the bartender, who nods.
The bartender places a drink, then nods towards the end of the bar. We turn to see Brendon Urie.
We twirl our thumbs, and look at the bartender, who looks elsewhere
Urie walks up and smiles smugly at us.
We push our glass of pink alcohol away. Urie puts his hand on our knees, and we slap his face.
We knock back orange liquid. He sips something brown, winces, and puts it aside.
We knock back several more drinks, and rub our fingers on his face.
He takes us across the bar, and grabs a champagne bottle off of a confused couple's table.
We dance with Urie. He dips us. We run our hands up and down his body.
He spins us.
He falls back to the floor, and gets up. We spin around in a blur of lights and colors.
He tries to kiss us, and we slap his face and wag our finger.
He looks down at us as we embrace and spin.
He runs his tongue up our arm.
He suddenly stops and looks down.
He sees our scaly tentacle between our legs.
His eyes widen and he stumbles back.
We slap our tentacle until it glitches and becomes invisible.
He wrap our arm around him, but he tries to shake us off.
We hand him a glass of white wine, a shot of red, a glass of brown, and a shot of clear
We help him stumble out of the bar.
We open an app on our phone, then beckon to Urie.
At night, at a house, we take Urie's jacket off. He struggles to remove his jacket.
We lock the door, then push him to the stairs.
He stumbles up the stairs and leans in for a kiss. We slap him, and he stumbles back down the hall.
He falls back onto the floor, resting against the bed. We throw lacy underwear at his face, and he smiles. The light from the hallway casts our shadow against his face.
The shadow of a naked woman with outstretched hands implodes in on itself, turning into a floating ball that erupts into tentacles. Urie pushes away, stopped by the bed.
We lean forward, and he bolts underneath us.
He races through the house in his underwear, as our slimy tentacles reach for him.
He throws a lamp at us, and we catch it with a tentacle.
We spin around, then toss the lamp back in his face. He falls to the ground.
He tries to slide backward, but a tentacle grabs his ankle.
In the bedroom, tentacles lift him up.
He is freaked out.
A 3rd tentacle pokes his nose, while a 4th stabs him in the back, emerging from his stomach.
He looks down in shock
We throw him through a window.
Looking over our balcony, we see his bloody, body on the sidewalk
We pick him up and eat him.
In the morning, our tentacles move blankets aside.
We throw up a skull into a trashcan
Our tentacles turn into arms
We put on a jacket and pants.
We look in the mirror, and we are Brendon Urie.
We do makeup. Our left arm becomes a tentacle, and we slap it until it turns back into an arm.
We open an app and a black car pulls up.
We enter a club.
We meet a woman in a red dress at the bar. We clink glasses.
We take the woman to the dance floor. We spin her, she dances, dropping to the floor then back up again.
We dip her. Our outstretched hand into a tentacle, and she screams. Cut to credits.
